      <h2>Shared Page — Compliance Overview (GL9SUSD + GL9XUSD)</h2>

      <h3>GODLEVEL9 Stablecoin Compliance Program</h3>
      <p><b>Applies to GL9SUSD (Septillion Series) and GL9XUSD (Sextillion Series)</b></p>
      <p>
        This page summarizes how GL9SUSD and GL9XUSD are operated with a compliance framework suitable for
        public stablecoin issuance and redemption. The goal is simple:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>protect holders</li>
        <li>prevent illicit use</li>
        <li>keep banking and redemption rails functional</li>
        <li>meet legal obligations where the program operates</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Note: Requirements vary by jurisdiction. Access to minting/redemption may be limited or unavailable in restricted regions.</p>

      <h3>1) What This Compliance Program Covers</h3>
      <p>This program applies to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Direct minting (issuer-side issuance to verified users/institutions)</li>
        <li>Direct redemption (issuer-side cash-out at par under policy terms)</li>
        <li>Issuer-controlled operations (reserve flows, banking rails, reporting)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This program does not necessarily apply to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>secondary market trading between third parties (which may occur on platforms that list the token), though sanctioned or prohibited addresses may be restricted where legally required.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2) Identity Verification (KYC / KYB)</h3>
      <p>To access direct minting or redemption, users must complete verification.</p>
      <p><b>Individuals (KYC)</b></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Government-issued ID verification</li>
        <li>Basic identity checks</li>
        <li>Risk screening</li>
      </ul>
      <p><b>Businesses (KYB)</b></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Entity registration validation</li>
        <li>Ownership/beneficial owner checks (where applicable)</li>
        <li>Authorized signatory verification</li>
        <li>Risk screening</li>
      </ul>
      <p><b>Why this exists</b></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Prevents fraud and abuse</li>
        <li>Supports banking and payment partner requirements</li>
        <li>Helps satisfy legal obligations in many jurisdictions</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3) Sanctions Screening</h3>
      <p>I screen users and transactions against sanctions and prohibited-party lists, consistent with applicable law.</p>
      <p>This can include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>screening at onboarding</li>
        <li>ongoing screening for changes</li>
        <li>screening at redemption/mint time</li>
        <li>screening of high-risk transaction patterns</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If sanctions risk is detected:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>access may be denied</li>
        <li>redemptions may be refused</li>
        <li>accounts may be suspended</li>
        <li>reporting may occur where required</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>4) AML Controls (Anti–Money Laundering)</h3>
      <p>I maintain AML controls to detect and prevent illicit finance.</p>
      <p>Controls include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>transaction monitoring</li>
        <li>velocity and volume analysis</li>
        <li>pattern detection for suspicious behavior</li>
        <li>enhanced due diligence for higher-risk users</li>
        <li>investigation and escalation workflows</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If a transaction is flagged:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>it may be delayed for review</li>
        <li>additional information may be requested</li>
        <li>redemption may be refused where required</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>5) Source-of-Funds / Source-of-Wealth (When Required)</h3>
      <p>For larger redemptions or higher risk categories, I may request:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>proof of source-of-funds (bank statements, business revenue records, etc.)</li>
        <li>source-of-wealth explanations (how funds were obtained)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This is used for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>fraud prevention</li>
        <li>risk management</li>
        <li>meeting legal or partner compliance standards</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>6) Prohibited Activity</h3>
      <p>I do not support activity involving:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>sanctioned entities or jurisdictions (as applicable)</li>
        <li>fraud, theft, or scam proceeds</li>
        <li>terrorist financing</li>
        <li>child exploitation material or related transactions</li>
        <li>trafficking-related proceeds</li>
        <li>ransomware payments (where prohibited)</li>
        <li>laundering attempts through structured redemptions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If prohibited activity is suspected, actions may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>account freeze/suspension</li>
        <li>refusal of service/redemption</li>
        <li>reporting where legally required</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>7) Data Handling & Retention</h3>
      <p>I collect only what is needed to operate safely and lawfully.</p>
      <p><b>Data types may include</b></p>
      <ul>
        <li>identity verification data (KYC/KYB)</li>
        <li>transaction logs and redemption records</li>
        <li>compliance review notes</li>
        <li>banking payout details for redemptions</li>
      </ul>
      <p><b>Retention</b></p>
      <ul>
        <li>retained for a defined period required by policy/law/partner standards</li>
        <li>secure storage practices are used</li>
        <li>access is restricted internally</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>8) Appeals & Dispute Process</h3>
      <p>If a user is denied redemption or access due to compliance review, I provide a process for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>requesting reconsideration (where allowed)</li>
        <li>submitting clarifying documentation</li>
        <li>escalating disputes through support/compliance channels</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Some cases may not allow disclosure of the reason due to legal restrictions.</p>

      <h3>9) Monitoring, Audits, and Internal Controls</h3>
      <p>I operate internal controls to reduce operational risk:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>role-based access controls (least privilege)</li>
        <li>multi-approval workflows for reserve movements</li>
        <li>logging and audit trails</li>
        <li>periodic internal reviews</li>
        <li>incident response procedures</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>10) Jurisdictional Limitations</h3>
      <p>Stablecoin services may not be available everywhere. I may restrict access based on:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>residency or location</li>
        <li>local regulation</li>
        <li>banking partner coverage</li>
        <li>sanctions requirements</li>
      </ul>

